-- Cook Scores 168 as England Defies India in First Cricket Test
-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 2012-11-18T12:20:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-18/cook-scores-168-as-england-defies-india-in-first-cricket-test.html
England captain  Alastair Cook  scored
an unbeaten century as his team took the first cricket Test
against India into a final day at Ahmedabad.  At stumps on the fourth day, England reached 340-5 in its
follow-on, including 168 by Cook in his first Test since being
appointed captain. Matt Prior is 84 not out in a stand of 141
runs with Cook.  Kevin Pietersen  was bowled for 2, his second dismissal in
the match to left-arm spinner Pragyan Ojha.  England, which resumed today at 111-0, has a lead of 10
runs after scoring 191 in its first innings. India made 521-8
declared, including 206 not out by Cheteshwar Pujara.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Christopher Elser at 
 celser@bloomberg.net  